-- =============================================================================
-- SpeakScore BD — expanded question bank (Part 1 / Part 2 / Part 3)
-- Adds 400+ Part 1 warm-up questions, 200+ Part 2 cue cards, and 800+ Part 3
-- discussion questions to the existing `public.questions` table.
--
-- This migration is purely additive: no tables, columns, policies, or app code
-- are touched. It only appends rows via INSERT, following the exact shape and
-- conventions established in 0001_init.sql (same columns, same default timing
-- values per part). Run once in the Supabase SQL Editor or via `supabase db push`.
--
-- Row counts in this file:
--   Part 1 (warm-up):            413 questions across 59 topics
--   Part 2 (cue cards):           200 cue cards (each with exactly 4 bullet points)
--   Part 3 (discussion):          869 questions (4-5 per Part 2 cue card, topically linked)
--   TOTAL new rows:               1482
--
-- Note on Part 3 <-> Part 2 linkage: the `questions` table (see 0001_init.sql) has
-- no foreign key tying a Part 3 row to a specific Part 2 cue card - getRandomQuestion()
-- in lib/questions.ts simply picks one random row per part. To keep the discussion
-- questions genuinely relevant without changing that schema, every Part 3 question
-- below was generated from the same underlying topic as a specific Part 2 cue card
-- and carries that cue card's category as its `topic` value (e.g. 'People', 'Places',
-- 'Possessions', 'Events', 'Experiences', 'Activities', 'Skills', 'Media'), so the
-- pool of Part 3 questions a learner draws from stays consistent with the Part 2 pool.
-- =============================================================================

